<L>__{interior newsroom late afternoon}
<A>__{aaron and ernie are off to the side in the newsroom people are packing their belongings as secretaries cry and embrace from an office rumbles a shouted denunciation:}
<C>__{anonymous voice}
<D>__{no. i won't keep my voice down. those sons of bitches...they are worse than accountants they are bad accountants.}
<A>__{tom enters scene.}
<C>__{tom}
<D>__{have you guys seen jane?}
<C>__{ernie}
<D>__{she's in there becoming the first woman bureau chief we've had here.}
<A>__{tom takes this in.}
<C>__{aaron}
<D>__{what did they do with you?}
<C>__{tom}
<D>__{they booted me out of washington.}
<C>__{aaron}
<D>__{impossible. there's no system that wouldn't value one of us.}
<C>__{tom}
<D>__{why? what did they do to you?}
<C>__{ernie}
<P>__{(pointing at aaron)}
<D>__{it's what he did. i'm proud of him.}
<C>__{aaron}
<D>__{they told me they'd keep me because they could plug me into any story and my salary was in line.}
<C>__{ernie}
<D>__{the cost efficient reporter.}
